{
  "texts": [
    "The word embeddings are generated against each dataset using a custom Python script and vectors are stored in text files.",
    "The DL model training is performed using Keras, a python-based library developed by Google which is widely used to perform various NLP-related tasks.",
    "A split ratio of 70-20-10% is used for each dataset for the training, testing, and validation.",
    "The optimal selection of parameters significantly impacts the overall performance of the DL models.",
    "Based on prior knowledge and after performing multiple experiments, the values of different parameters are fine-tuned."
  ]
}